The extreme and potentially lethal game of Russian roulette has been reinvented with Taser guns taking the place of the previously used live ammunition.

The updated version of the game was founded by Valeriy Eshenko, and is rapidly growing in popularity in the Russian city of Perm.

Modelled on the original game, Valeriy’s version features Tasers with an amperage of 0.1W being used in the first round raising to 0.4W used in the last.

